# PR Preparation Workflow

Invoke with: *"prepare PR"*, *"ready for review"*, *"PR checklist"*, *"before I submit"*

Follow this workflow before creating a pull request.

---

## 1. Code Completion Check

### Feature Complete
- [ ] All requirements met
- [ ] Edge cases handled
- [ ] Error scenarios covered

### No Unfinished Work
- [ ] No TODO comments without context
- [ ] No commented-out code
- [ ] No console.log statements
- [ ] No debug code left
- [ ] No hardcoded test data

---

## 2. Code Quality Checks

### Build
```bash
npm run build
```

### TypeScript
- [ ] No type errors
- [ ] No implicit `any` types
- [ ] Explicit return types on exported functions
- [ ] Proper null/undefined handling

---

## 3. Self Code Review

### Developer Perspective

**Code Structure**
- [ ] Single responsibility followed
- [ ] Logic extracted to appropriate modules
- [ ] Files under 200 lines
- [ ] Proper folder organization

**Code Quality**
- [ ] No code duplication
- [ ] Descriptive naming
- [ ] No magic numbers (use constants)
- [ ] Consistent patterns with codebase

**Error Handling**
- [ ] All async operations have error handling
- [ ] Route handlers use try/catch/next
- [ ] User-friendly error messages in API responses
- [ ] External service failures handled gracefully

### QE Perspective

**Edge Cases**
- [ ] Empty data handled
- [ ] Null/undefined handled
- [ ] Invalid input returns proper errors

**External Services**
- [ ] Service unavailability handled
- [ ] Timeout handling on HTTP calls

### Security Perspective

**Input/Output**
- [ ] Route params/query/body validated
- [ ] SQL uses parameterized queries
- [ ] No sensitive data in responses
- [ ] Error messages don't leak internals

**Configuration**
- [ ] No hardcoded secrets
- [ ] New config uses environment variables

---

## 4. Commit Hygiene

### Commit Structure
- [ ] Meaningful commit messages
- [ ] Logical, atomic commits
- [ ] No broken commits in history

### Commit Message Format
```
<type>: <short summary>

<longer description if needed>
```

**Types**
- `feat`: New feature
- `fix`: Bug fix
- `refactor`: Code change that neither fixes nor adds
- `chore`: Maintenance tasks
- `docs`: Documentation changes

---

## 5. PR Description

### Template
```markdown
## Description

> Brief description of changes

## Changes

- Added/Modified/Removed X
- Added/Modified/Removed Y

## Testing

> How this was tested

## Configuration

> Any new environment variables or config changes
```

---

## 6. Deployment Considerations

- [ ] K8s manifests updated if needed
- [ ] ConfigMap/Secret updated if new env vars
- [ ] Dockerfile changes (if dependencies changed)
- [ ] README updated if needed

---

## 7. Final Checklist

### Code
- [ ] Build passes (`npm run build`)
- [ ] No debug code
- [ ] Self-reviewed

### PR
- [ ] Descriptive title
- [ ] Complete description
- [ ] Testing documented

### Ready
- [ ] Branch up-to-date with main
- [ ] Commits clean
- [ ] Ready for review

---

## Quick Commands

```bash
npm run build            # Full compile check
```
